article.story: MORAGA, Calif. -- — Augustas Marciulionis scored 18 points as Saint Mary's (CA) beat Northern Kentucky 92-56 on Thursday. Marciulionis added eight assists for the Gaels (8-5). Joshua Jefferson scored 15 points and added 12 rebounds. Mitchell Saxen shot 5 of 10 from the field to finish with 12 points. The Norse (7-6) were led in scoring by Trey Robinson, who finished with 14 points. Northern Kentucky also got 14 points from Marques Warrick. Michael Bradley also recorded 10 points. Saint Mary's (CA) plays Saturday against Missouri State at home, and Northern Kentucky visits Purdue Fort Wayne on Friday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
